<br>
This would mean that a guild who breaks rotation rules misses one turn at that rotation. Most of the guilds involved are fairly relaxed and are almost always willing to offer a little leeway to other guilds. However, this leeway does not extend to guilds killing mobs out of order as this should never happen. If you have any doubts as to whether it is your turn or not, you should speak to the other guilds concerned.<br>
<br>
If punishments are not enforced on guilds that break rules, then in the future it will create a situation where people may kill a mob when it is not their turn because they can see it wielding a specific weapon or something. If there are no real punishments for doing this, then there is nothing stopping this from happening.<br>
<br>
As far as the RTA being able to enforce punishments, I don't think this is an issue. The RTA is not just half a dozen admins, it is a collection of guilds on the server. If someone refuses to accept punishments decided by the other guilds on that rotation, then there would be the possibility that the other guilds may decide to revoke the perpetrator's rotation rights.<br>
<br>
It may sound harsh, but for a system to work, there must be rules which are enforceable and consequences if those rules are not followed.<br>
<br>
